social_posts.post_text:
say it with me: cherry yum-yum (cherry miam-miam for all my francophones). 🍒

I grew up eating it every year for Christmas. Nannie would always make it with this powdery stuff called Dream Whip, so i took her recipe (foolproof replica pictured above, along with my feeble attempt at a bake-off drawing) and modernized it a bit, taking care to not squander its inherent charm: how easy and delicious it is. ✨ graham cracker crust, cream cheese filling, cherry pie filling ✨ how easy is that?! after reading comments I’m so excited to see how much of a family staple some version of this is for folks all over. it’s the ultimate choose-your-own-adventure dessert: flavorings, cookie crusts, pie fillings. make it work for you! two fun facts: the recipe published on what would’ve been Nannie’s 92nd birthday last Thursday, and @bwashbu inadvertently channeled her when he styled these amazing photos with white wine. she would be so astounded, and so so proud. 💖 please go watch the video linked in stories and in my bio!

*dame julie andrews voice* these are a few of my favo(u)rite cakes… that i made this year for ppl i love🫡 ft. a disco ball that survived a long car ride, a chanel bag that survived an even longer car ride, a couple butter mochis, a terrarium and a partridge in a pear tree
cooooooookie! I made the famed @nytimes @davidleite ccc 🍪… a bunch of times, a bunch of different ways, to see what version is the best. hey, you! yeah, you! go check it out at the linque in baïeau!

hey do u like grilled cheese? yes, chef! well then go watch my video about finding the perfect one — I made myself absolutely ill in the process! 💝

✨ link in bio AND stories if you’re lucky enough to catch those. thank you to @adamology for producing, @ameliaarend for grating so much cheese for me + the rest of the crew for putting up with my unhinged descent into madness.

how YOU doin! well, you should probably stop WHAT you’re doin and sign up for my cookie week newsletter 🍪🍪🍪 the first one goes out tomorrow and runs for *10 whole days.* can you imagine? who let me have access to a keyboard?! they may regret it, but you won’t 😈 (link in bio to sign up, or just google “cookie week newsletter”)

glittery, nuanced, molten inside and a spicy kick on the back end. ok enough about me, let’s talk about these cookies! 

for cookie week this year, I give you the Mexican hot chocolate cookie. as a leo with a gemini rising and a scorpio moon, this cookie really is me. at first glance, it sparkles but also runs hot and cold (leo, gemini). then, when you really sit with it, the spiciness creeps up on you (scorpio). plus, the cinnamon in the dough and in the sugar coating will make your kitchen smell 💋💋❤️‍🔥. happy cookie week to all, and very happy baking miluvs! 

profesh photos by @johnny_miller_ , styling by @samanthaseneviratne. big ups to @pmelnick for producing the hale out of these videos and a very big shoutout to @brownedbutterblondie whose trick of freezing the marshmallows pulled me out of an existential crisis! there are.. so many more folks to than but i’m running out of room and my fingers are cramping. 🎅🏼
